tool.name: EEMSModelRun

param.name: FinalOutputField
param.dialogReference: The final output field in the EEMS model. This parameter only serves to ensure that the model is executed after all the model commands have been written to the EEMS Command File.

param.name: OutputReportingUnits
param.dialogReference: The path to the final EEMS output feature class.

param.name: InputReportingUnits
param.dialogReference: The path to the Input Reporting Units. In most cases, you should not change this value as the default entry (%EEMS Input Table Path%) is a variable that stores the path to the input reporting units defined in EEMS Model Initialization Tool.

param.name: EEMSCommandFile
param.dialogReference: The path to the EEMS command file. Do not change this value, as the default entry (%EEMS Command File Path%) is a variable that stores the path to the EEMS Command File defined in EEMS Model Initialization Tool.

tool.summary:
Runs the EEMS model by performing the following tasks:

  1. Copies the input reporting units to the output reporting units.

  2. Creates a CSV file from the input reporting units.

  3. Calls MPilot to execute the commands in the EEMS command file on the CSV.

  4. Joins the results back to the output reporting units.
